.. This changelog follows the format at https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/ ; this project adheres to Semantic Versioning.
    Added      for new features.
    Changed    for changes in existing functionality.
    Deprecated for soon-to-be removed features.
    Removed    for now removed features.
    Fixed      for any bug fixes.
    Security   in case of vulnerabilities.
    Docs       for any documentation changes


[0.4.0] - 2026-05-08
---------------------

**Added**:
    - Generic documentation system: every immediate subdirectory of ``docs/``
      is now treated as an independent documentation unit.  There is no longer
      a fixed set of names — subdirectory names are freely choosable.  All
      units are discovered and built automatically; no configuration is needed
      to add a new unit.

    - Engine auto-detection: the documentation engine for each unit is
      determined by inspecting its contents.  A ``source/conf.py`` file
      selects Sphinx; a ``mkdocs.yml`` selects MkDocs (detected but not yet
      built — a warning is logged and the unit is skipped).  Units whose
      directory matches neither marker also produce a warning and are skipped.

    - ``[docs]`` section in ``builder.toml``:

      - ``dist_dirs`` — list of subdirectory names whose built HTML is copied
        into the distribution artefacts (``dist/pyinstaller/documentation/<name>/``).
        Defaults to ``[]`` (no documentation distributed).

      - ``apidoc_dirs`` — list of subdirectory names that require a
        ``sphinx-apidoc`` pre-pass before ``sphinx-build``.  Defaults to
        ``[]``.  This replaces the previously hardcoded behaviour of always
        running ``sphinx-apidoc`` for a directory named ``developer_guide``.

    - ``DocEngine`` enum and ``_detect_engine()`` function in
      ``scaldys_builder.common.docs``, providing a testable, reusable engine
      detection primitive.

    - ``WindowsBuilder._any_sphinx_docs()`` helper: replaces the hardcoded
      check for ``docs/manual/`` when determining whether Sphinx must be
      present at pre-flight time.

**Changed**:
    - Distribution path for documentation changed from the single fixed
      destination ``dist/pyinstaller/documentation/help files/`` to
      ``dist/pyinstaller/documentation/<name>/`` (one sub-folder per entry in
      ``[docs] dist_dirs``).

      .. note::
         **Breaking change for consuming projects.**  Any Inno Setup ``.iss``
         script that references the old ``documentation\help files\`` path
         must be updated to reference ``documentation\<name>\`` instead.

    - ``DocumentationBuilder`` refactored: the two hardcoded methods
      ``build_user_guide()`` and ``build_developer_guide()`` are replaced by
      a generic ``build()`` / ``_build_one()`` / ``_build_sphinx()`` loop
      that works for any number of doc units.

    - ``BaseBuildEnvironment`` no longer exposes the four hardcoded path
      attributes ``user_guide_dir_path``, ``user_guide_build_dir_path``,
      ``developer_guide_dir_path``, and ``developer_guide_build_dir_path``.
      Paths are now derived at call-time from the directory name.

    - Documentation updated throughout: *Documentation Building* guide
      rewritten for the generic system; *Configuration* guide updated with
      the new ``[docs]`` section; *Project Layout*, *CLI Reference*,
      *Overview*, *Quick Start*, and *Windows Installer* pages updated to
      reflect the new paths and behaviour.



[0.3.0] - 2026-05-07
---------------------

**Added**:
    - Project compliance checking: ``scaldys-builder`` now validates the target
      project's required files and structure before running any build step.  All
      issues are reported together in a single pass so they can be fixed at once.
      If any requirement is not met the tool exits cleanly with a descriptive
      message rather than failing mid-build with a cryptic error.

      Compliance is checked automatically at the start of ``build windows exe``,
      ``build windows installer``, and ``build windows all``.

    - New top-level command ``scaldys-builder check``: runs the full compliance
      check on the current project without triggering a build.  Useful for
      verifying a freshly cloned project or diagnosing issues.

    - New documentation page *Project Compliance* (In-Depth Guides section):
      lists all eight compliance rules with descriptions, the commands each rule
      applies to, and cross-reference links to the relevant guide sections.

**Fixed**:
    - Project names containing hyphens (e.g. ``my-app``) are now normalised to
      underscores when resolving Python package paths (e.g. ``src/my_app/``,
      ``my_app/__main__.py``, ``--collect-submodules my_app``), matching the
      Python import system convention (PEP 503 / PEP 508).  The raw project name
      is preserved for artefact naming (executable, ``.iss`` script, launcher
      scripts, icon).


[0.2.0] - 2026-05-04
---------------------

**Added**:
    - Sphinx-based user manual under ``docs/manual/``, structured in three sections:

      *Users*

        - Overview — what ``scaldys-builder`` does, the build pipeline diagram,
          and two clear entry paths (new project vs. existing project)
        - Installation — adding ``scaldys-builder`` as a dev dependency with
          extras, external tool requirements, and installation verification
        - Quick Start — step-by-step project setup and first build walkthrough
        - CLI Reference — complete reference for every command and option
        - In-Depth Guides: project layout and build output, ``builder.toml``
          configuration, documentation building, Cython compilation, Windows
          EXE bundling, and Inno Setup installer creation

      *Developers*

        - Architecture — module layout, three-class composition pattern,
          execution flow, configuration loading, and an explanation of why
          ``compile_runner.py`` runs as a subprocess
        - Extension Points — design conventions and how to add Cython modules,
          build steps, or a new platform builder
        - Contributing — dev environment setup, testing, linting, publishing,
          and testing changes against a consuming project

      *About*

        - Changelog, authors, license, and get-help page

    - ``docs/manual/Makefile`` and ``make.bat`` for building the HTML manual
    - ``licenses/`` directory with license copies and credit information for
      all third-party tools used by ``scaldys-builder``
    - ``licenses/README.md`` index listing each tool's license type, upstream
      URL, and link to the corresponding local license file

**Changed**:
    - Project version bumped to 0.2.0 in ``pyproject.toml``


[0.1.1] - 2025-xx-xx
---------------------

**Changed**:
    - Added ``uv.lock`` for reproducible dependency resolution
    - Minor corrections based on Pyright feedback


[0.1.0] - (unreleased)
-----------------------

**Added**:
    - Initial release extracted from scaldys-template
    - Modular build system: common base, Windows builder, Sphinx docs, Cython runner
    - ``builder.toml`` for per-project build configuration (compiled modules, packaging paths)
    - ``compile_runner`` module replaces project-level ``compile.py`` scripts
